column1:
What's the case for Zoom recovering though? Teams is the behemoth, and if you're on Office 365 it'd be silly not to use it. If you aren't on MS you're probably on Google, in which case you'd just use Google Meet. 

There's still a market for Zoom in the same way that Teams isn't going to entirely kill Slack, but I don't see Zoom getting anywhere close to back to the COVID-era peak.
